ronment because `amm` is not installed.\n- `robot convert`: attempted after edits, but could not run in this environment because `robot` is not installed.\n\n## Checklist\n\n- [x] PLAN: Issue context and comments reviewed; requester intent was clear.\n- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: Attempted `make travis_build`; blocked by missing `amm`.\n- [x] RESEARCH: `RESEARCH.md` created; PMID:25265334 validated.\n- [x] TERM-SEARCH: Existing GO terms `GO:0180067` and `GO:0180069` inspected with `obo-grep.pl`.\n- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md` created from relevant biosynthetic and positive-regulation patterns.\n- [x] EDITS: Used `obo-checkout.pl`, edited files in `terms/`, and checked changes back in with `obo-checkin.pl`.\n- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: Existing logical definitions retained; `CHEBI:233617 ! terreate` retained for pH 7.3 chemical form.\n- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: Used chemical-entity guidance. Obsoletion, mapping, reaction, and taxon-constraint workflows were not applicable.\n- [x] METADATA: Term tracker links retained; requested `created_by` values changed to `GOC:vw`.\n- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: Full validation attempted but blocked by missing local tools; lightweight diff and reference validation passed.\n- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: PMID:25265334 validated with `linkml-reference-validator`.\n- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: Committed local ontology change.\nChanges committed in PR #<NN>.\n\nI updated the affected terreic acid terms so the primary labels use `terreic acid`, with `terreate` retained as related synonyms where appropriate. The logical definition still uses `CHEBI:233617 ! terreate`, consistent with the pH 7.3 chemical-entity convention. I also changed the requested `created_by` values from `PomBase:vw` to `GOC:vw`.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
